#include <iostream>
#include <string>

using namespace std;

string month[] = {"JAN", "FEB", "MAR", "APR", "MAY", "JUN", "JUL", "AUG", "SEP", "OCT", "NOV", "DEC"};
int leap[] = {31, 29, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31};
int nonLeap[] = {31, 28, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31};

int main(){
	int test;
	cin>>test;
	string input;
	int d,y,index,days,c=1;

	bool flag;
	while(test--){
		cin>>input;
		string m;
		d = (input[0]-'0')*10 + (input[1]-'0');
		for(int i=0; i<3; i++)
			m.push_back(input[i+3]);
		y = (input[7]-'0')*1000 + (input[8]-'0')*100 + (input[9]-'0')*10 + (input[10]-'0');

		for(int i=0; i<12; i++){
		    if(m.compare(month[i])==0){
		        index = i;
		        break;
		    }
		}
		//cout<<d<<m<<y<<endl;
		days=0;
		flag=false;
		if(y%4==0){
			if(y%100==0){
				if(y%400==0)
					flag=true;
			}
			else
			flag=true;
		}
		if(flag){
			for(int i=0; i<index; i++)
				days += leap[i];
		}
		else{
			for(int i=0; i<index; i++)
				days += nonLeap[i];
		}
		days += d;

		cout<<"Case "<<c<<": ";
		if(days<=300)
			cout<<days<<" Hundreds";
		else if(days<=360)
			cout<<days-300<<" Tens";
		else
			cout<<days-360<<" Ones";
		cout<<endl;
		c++;
	}
}
